that had a fair market value of $127 million.
2) the company exchanged 43 percent ownership in 3m inter-unitek gmbh,
previously a wholly owned 3m subsidiary, for 87 percent of espe dental ag.  in
2001, 3m also paid $25 million in cash (net of cash acquired) such that 3m
inter-unitek gmbh owned 100 percent of the outstanding shares of espe dental
ag.  the value of the non-cash transaction in 2001 was estimated at
approximately $245 million.  in 2002, 3m purchased the 43 percent minority
ownership in 3m inter-unitek gmbh for approximately $304 million.  the
difference in these values relates to exchange rate changes and the strong
performance of the business.  refer to note 3 in the consolidated financial
statements for additional information about these transactions.
