note 17.  management stock ownership program
in may 2002, shareholders approved 22.7 million shares for issuance under the
management stock ownership program (msop) in the form of management stock
options, restricted stock and stock appreciation rights.  under the plan, the
company has principally issued management stock options that are granted at
market value at the date of grant. these options generally are exercisable one
year after the date of grant and expire 10 years from the date of grant.  thus,
outstanding shares under option include grants from previous plans.  there were
14,210 participants in the plan at december 31, 2002.
