item 14.  controls and procedures
a.  within the 90 days prior to the filing date of this annual report, the
company carried out an evaluation, under the supervision and with the
participation of the company's management, including the company's chief
executive officer and chief financial officer, of the effectiveness of the
design and operation of the company's disclosure controls and procedures
pursuant to exchange act rule 13a-14.  based upon that evaluation, the chief
executive officer and chief financial officer concluded that the company's
disclosure controls and procedures are effective in timely alerting them to
material information relating to the company (including its consolidated
subsidiaries) required to be included in the company's periodic sec filings.
b.  there have been no significant changes in the company's internal controls
or in other factors that could significantly affect internal controls
subsequent to the date the company carried out this evaluation.
